<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="374" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1653,2019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1786,1811]" pageId="1" pageNumber="374">Description.</emphasis>
Forewings dark yellow with two oblique bands: proximal consists of three brownish spots, distal—of three slightly curved streaks; along the outer margin there are three double pairs of spots; an outer space of the proximal band is brownish darkened in hind half. Hindwing entirely yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1653,2019]" box="[199,1347,1886,1911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="374">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1886,1911]" pageId="1" pageNumber="374">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,468,1886,1911]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1839]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 14. Lithosiinae moths (7 – 9, 11), their labels (10) and male genitalia (12 – 14). 7 — Paraheliosia rufa (Leech, 1890), male, China, Gansu, Kang Xian; 8 — Paraheliosia rufa ussuriensis (O. Bang-Haas, 1927), male, Russia, Primorskiy Kray, 20 km E from Kirovskiy; 9 – 10 — Paraheliosia novirufa (Fang, 1992), holotype, male (9), China, Zhejiang, Zhoushan, and its labels (10); 11, 12 — Nudina artaxidia (Butler, 1881), male, Russia, Blagoveshchensk; 13 — Paraheliosia elegans (Reich, 1937), holotype, China, Zhejiang, West Tien Mu Shan; 14 — Paraheliosia rufa ussuriensis (O. Bang-Haas, 1927), Russia, Primorskiy Kray, 20 km E from Kirovskiy." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224838/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="374">
